# Cleanup Obsolete Code

After implementing or refactoring a major feature, feel free to remove code and files that are clearly obsolete and no longer used.

## What To Clean Up

- Dead components, helpers, routes, and utilities
- Stale imports, types, and unreachable branches
- Old files replaced by the new implementation
- Outdated paths and references left behind by refactors

## Safety Rules

- Verify references before deleting anything
- Prefer removing clearly unused code in the same change rather than leaving drift behind
- Do not delete files when ownership or current usage is uncertain
- Do not remove user changes that are unrelated to the task
